items.name: Young Dracula Wiki
items.title: Young Dracula Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Young Dracula Wiki
items.desc: Young Dracula Wiki is a fan created encyclopaedia which covers all aspects of the CBBC television series Young Dracula. The series follows the Dracula family: Vladimir, his father Count Dracula, and older sister Ingrid. Here you will find out about the characters, places, episodes and actors from the programme.

items.name: The Young and the Restless Wiki
items.title: The Young and the Restless Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to The Young and the Restless Wikia!
items.desc: The Young and the Restless Wikia is a collaborative project to create the most definitive, accurate and accessible encyclopedia and reference for everything related to Y&R. This English-language Wikia started in June 2010. If this is your first visit, please check out the FAQ to help get you started. The wiki format allows anyone to create or edit any article, so we can all work together to create the site! Have fun!

items.name: Young cash09 Wiki
items.title: Young cash09 Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to The Future Heroes and Horrors Movies
items.desc: The Future Heroes and Horrors Movies wiki is a fan community dedicated to horror and hero films, past and future. Interested in creating fan fiction for a horror film? Want to create an article page for your favorite series? This place is open to everyone. Feel free to hop on in and contribute to the wiki!

items.name: Young Samurai Wiki
items.title: Young Samurai Wiki
items.desc: Young Samurai is a book series written by Chris Bradford that documents Jack Fletcher's training as a samurai and his quest to reach the port city of Nagasaki to catch a ship bound for England. Many dangers await Jack on his journey, but despite the perils, the journey is rewarding - along the way, he forges bonds with friends he will never forget and learns the way of the warrior.

items.name: Young Justice Wiki
items.title: Young Justice Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Young Justice Wiki
items.desc: The Young Justice Wiki is a Wiki intended to cover all aspects of the Young Justice TV series that debuted in 2010 as well as its tie-in comics. This Wiki contains extensive character biographies, episode recaps, articles about places, dates, etc., and provides an exhaustive coverage of trivia, in and out of universe references, and keeps track of the latest news about this franchise!

items.name: Mr young Wiki
items.title: Mr young Wiki
items.headline: Learn More about Mr. Young Wikia!
items.desc: The Mr. Young Wikia is a community site dedicated to the Mr. Young Canadian comedy TV series. This highschool sitcom lasted from 2011 to 2013. If you are a fan of this series, just curious about it, or a fan of high-school sitcoms then this is the place for you! We would like the old fans to come back. At the moment, this wikia doesn't have web traffic, so we are hoping through this advertisement to gain some web traffic. Although it might be a stretch because the show's buzz has died down from its cancellation, we can always try. If you are new to this show, access might be limited on the web. However, you are welcome to watch it on Youtube for most episodes, watch on Netflix, or purchase the series volumes on the Apple Store. Please come and explore our content and help us maybe to expand this database... or join us in discussion about the characters, the episodes, or the series in general. Thanks for reading this ad!

items.title: Young Justice RP Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to Young Justice Roleplaying Wiki
items.desc: This is a wiki dedicated to Role-Playing in the DC Universe. You can create your own characters and interact with other characters. Originally this wiki was focused on the Young Justice team, however recently we have branched out into the entire DC Universe! You can have multiple characters, all doing some of the many things available, such as: Missions, Young Romance, Saving the Day (Or ruining it!) and many other things. As the community grows so will the ideas so come one and come all.

items.name: Young Justice Legacy Wiki
items.title: Young Justice Legacy Wiki
items.headline: Young Justice Legacy Wiki
items.desc: Young Justice Legacy Wiki is a wiki dedicated to making interesting and enticing Young Justice fan fiction. This can include creating your own "Team" member or going off on your own and making your own custom team. You can also create your own Justice League member or Super villain to combat members of the Justice League and "The Team". Most importantly, though, one should remember to always have as much fun as possible.

items.name: YoungWritersClub Wiki
items.title: YoungWritersClub Wiki
items.headline: Is Writing your hobby or a Passion?
items.desc: Are you a budding writer or looking for some inspiration with your work? The Young Writers Club Wiki is mainly aimed at teenagers, and this site can also be used for advice if you are looking to persue a career in writing. Our Admins are ready and willing to help anybody out on maybe some writing tips or if you have a problem with another user we will jump into action to make sure that problem gets resolved quickly. You can post a piece of your work, get advice on it and critiques and much more!

items.headline: Join the Realistic Wolf Role Play
items.desc:
This is a realistic role play based on real wolf behaviour, the roleplay takes place in Slough Creek, Yellowstone National Park. You are free to choose between two different packs, you can stay as loner for a few time as well.  As our roleplay is realistic this means your wolf appearance must be too. 
At the moment we have around 29 members in the site. You can either create your own wolf and/or adopt one of the available wolves, Join!

items.name: Younger Wiki
items.title: Younger Wiki
items.desc: Liza is a 40-year-old recently divorced mother looking to get a job, which proves difficult for a woman of her age. After a compliment from a much younger man Josh, she decides to get a makeover, courtesy of her friend Maggie, in order to look like she is in her mid-twenties. Ultimately, she becomes an assistant to Diana (Miriam Shor) in a publishing firm, who pairs her with co-worker Kelsey. It is an American comedy-drama series on TVLand that premiered on March 31, 2015.
